The Federal Aviation Administrationsaid it expected continued growth for commercial aviation inthe next 12 years, with passenger traffic increasing at anannual rate of 4.5 pct on major scheduled airlines and 6.7 pcton commuter airlines.    However, the FAA forecast projects slower growth forgeneral aviation than for the air carriers.    The number of hours flown by private and business flyers,for example, is expected to grow at an annaul rate of less thanone pct compared with a six pct rate in the 1960s and 1970s. REUTER&#3;